OL,3,C'Profound injustice' for woman who had
OL,4,Chysterectomy without giving consent
OL,6,FBetsi Cadwalader University Health
OL,7,FBoard and Liverpool University
OL,8,FHospitals NHS Foundation Trust, have
OL,9,Fbeen criticised for 'multiple
OL,10,Ffailings' towards a woman who had a
OL,11,Fhysterectomy performed on her, without
OL,12,Fgiving informed consent for the
OL,13,Fsurgery.
OL,15,F'Ms A' as she is being referred to in
OL,16,Forder to protect her identity, had no
OL,17,Fprior discussion with health officials
OL,18,Fabout the procedure and only signed a
OL,19,Fconsent form on the day of her surgery.
