OL,3,C'Profound injustice' for woman who had
OL,4,Chysterectomy without giving consent
OL,6,FThe Ombudsman said this led to Ms A
OL,7,Fhaving persistent infection and ill
OL,8,Fhealth for nearly three years before
OL,9,Fshe received surgical treatment in
OL,10,FMarch 2022.
OL,12,FWithin its investigation, the
OL,13,FOmbudsman said it was concerned the
OL,14,FHealth Board's focus and priority was
OL,15,Fon its financial reporting of the
OL,16,Fcommissioned care and did not include
OL,17,Fan assessment of the quality of the
OL,18,Fcare and treatment delivered.
