OL,3,C'Profound injustice' for woman who had
OL,4,Chysterectomy without giving consent
OL,6,FMichelle Morris, the Public Services
OL,7,FOmbudsman for Wales, has said she is
OL,8,Fmindful of the "profound injustice
OL,9,Fcaused to Ms A as a result of the
OL,10,Fsignificant failings that have
OL,11,Foccurred in her case.
OL,13,F"I am extremely concerned about the
OL,14,Fprocess by which Ms A gave her
OL,15,F"consent" for the surgery in March
OL,16,F2022. The relevant guidance makes it
OL,17,Fclear that consent is not simply a
OL,18,Fmatter of completing and signing a
OL,19,Fform.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@IO]
