OL,3,C'Profound injustice' for woman who had
OL,4,Chysterectomy without giving consent
OL,6,F"Instead, consent is a process which
OL,7,Fshould begin well in advance of the
OL,8,Fday of the surgery and any discussions
OL,9,Fshould be clearly and separately
OL,10,Frecorded as part of the consenting
OL,11,Fprocess. This did not happen here.
OL,13,F"This sad case also highlighted the
OL,14,Fwholly inadequate contract monitoring
OL,15,Farrangements in place at the Health
OL,16,FBoard. Public bodies must have robust
OL,17,Fgovernance arrangements and must
OL,18,Fensure that patient safety and the
OL,19,Fmonitoring of the quality of services
OL,20,Fis in place.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/11
