OL,3,C'Profound injustice' for woman who had
OL,4,Chysterectomy without giving consent
OL,6,F"The Health Board's failure to monitor
OL,7,Fpatient safety and service quality led
OL,8,Fto it missing crucial opportunities to
OL,9,Faddress poor performance. With more
OL,10,Feffective contract monitoring, many of
OL,11,Fthese failings could have been
OL,12,Fprevented."
OL,14,FFrom its report the Ombudsman has made
OL,15,Ffive recommendations for the Health
OL,16,FBoard to implement:
OL,18,FThe Ombudsman says BCUHB has accepted
OL,19,Fthe recommendations, with the CEO of
OL,20,Fthe health board, Carol Shillabeer
OL,21,Fsaying lessons will be learnt.
