OL,3,C'Profound injustice' for woman who had
OL,4,Chysterectomy without giving consent
OL,6,F"I sincerely apologise for this
OL,7,Fpatient's poor experience and the
OL,8,FBoard is fully committed to taking
OL,9,Fforward learning from this case.
OL,11,F"It is essential for the health of our
OL,12,Fpopulation, we work with other health
OL,13,Fboards and trusts. It is clear we need
OL,14,Fto improve our oversight arrangements
OL,15,Ffor these commissioned services and we
OL,16,Ffully accept the Ombudsman's findings.
OL,18,F"We have already started to make those
OL,19,Fimprovements and our new commissioning
OL,20,Fapproach will help that further."
